# Semgrep ignore file — exclude paths that produce false positives.
#
# Rationale : security rules (detect-non-literal-fs-filename, non-literal-regexp,
# non-literal-require, etc.) routinely false-positive on test code that
# legitimately uses dynamic paths, regex constructed from fixtures, or
# parameterized fs reads. Tests are not production attack surface.
#
# Established standard : Semgrep, ESLint security plugin, and SonarQube all
# recommend excluding `__tests__/`, `tests/`, and `*.test.{ts,tsx}` patterns
# from security-rule scans.

# Test directories anywhere in the tree
**/__tests__/**
**/tests/**
**/test/**

# Test files by suffix
*.test.ts
*.test.tsx
*.test.js
*.test.jsx
*.spec.ts
*.spec.tsx
*.spec.js
*.spec.jsx

# Test helpers / fixtures
**/test-utils/**
**/test-helpers/**
**/__mocks__/**
**/fixtures/**

# Generated code (already auto-produced from authoritative sources)
**/generated/**
**/*.generated.ts
